{{Conjecture|legends}}
A group of '''fighters''' were loyal, pro-[[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] [[Homeworld/Legends|indigenous]] to [[Rotas V]],<ref name="RotSVD">''[[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]].<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> Rotan soldiers wore [[Kama/Legends|''kama'']] belt-spats, flexible [[Leather/Legends|leather]]<ref name="GttGAR">{{InsiderCite|84|Guide to the Grand Army of the Republic}}</ref> half-kilts<ref name="Revelation">''[[Legacy of the Force: Revelation]]''</ref> traditionally used by and associated with [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] warriors.<ref name="GttGAR" />

When many of the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic's]] [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone trooper]] [[Officer/Legends|officers]] took to wearing ''kamas'' due to the [[Army/Legends|army's]] Mandalorian influence, several Republic leaders were against the proliferation of a symbol from the Mandalorian culture among the [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] ranks. However, opinions were swayed into support after it was pointed out that the indigenous Republic fighters of [[Rotas system/Legends|Rotas]] V had also worn ''kamas'' into battle.<ref name="GttGAR" /> Referring to the ''kamas'' only as "[[Commander/Legends|command skirts]]," these individuals emphasized the influence of the Rotan fighters in the clones' usage of the ''kama''<ref name="RotSVD" /> over that of the Mandalorians.<ref name="GttGAR" />

==Behind the scenes==
The indigenous fighters of Rotas V were first introduced to ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]] in the [[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith: The Visual Dictionary|''Visual Dictionary'']] accompaniment to [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']]. They were later mentioned again in the ''[[Guide to the Grand Army of the Republic]]'', an article in the [[Star Wars Insider 84|eighty-fourth issue]] of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine, written by [[Karen Traviss]] and [[Ryan Kaufman (real person)|Ryan Kaufman]].

